REMARK 280 CRYSTALLIZATION CONDITIONS: MPRO WAS THAWED AND DILUTED TO 6 MG/ML   
REMARK 280  USING 20 MM HEPES PH 7.5, 50 MM NACL. THE LIGAND OF INTEREST WAS    
REMARK 280  DISSOLVED IN DMSO TO 10 MM AND THEN DILUTED INTO THE PROTEIN        
REMARK 280  SOLUTION TO A FINAL CONCENTRATION OF 1 MM. THE LIGAND WAS THEN      
REMARK 280  ALLOWED TO INCUBATE WITH THE PROTEIN FOR TWO HOURS AT ROOM          
REMARK 280  TEMPERATURE PRIOR TO DISPENSING PLATES. THE DROP COMPOSITION WAS    
REMARK 280  0.15 UL PROTEIN LIGAND SOLUTION, 0.3 UL 11% (V/V) PEG 4K, 0.1 M     
REMARK 280  MES PH 6.5, AND 0.05 UL MPRO CRYSTAL SEED STOCK. THE MPRO           
REMARK 280  CRYSTAL SEED STOCK WAS PREPARED BY CRUSHING MPRO CRYSTALS WITH A    
REMARK 280  PIPETTE TIP, SUSPENDING THEM IN 30% PEG 4K, 5% (V/V) DMSO, 0.1 M    
REMARK 280  MES PH 6.5, AND VORTEXING FOR 60 S WITH APPROXIMATELY 10 GLASS      
REMARK 280  BEADS (1.0 MM DIAMETER, BIOSPEC PRODUCTS). RESERVOIR SOLUTION       
REMARK 280  WAS 11PC (V/V) PEG 4K, 5PC (V/V) DMSO, 0.1 M MES PH 6.5.            
REMARK 280  CRYSTALS WERE GROWN USING THE SITTING DROP VAPOR DIFFUSION          
REMARK 280  METHOD AT 20 DEGREES C AND APPEARED WITHIN 24 HOURS, REACHING       
REMARK 280  FULL SIZE WITHIN 36 HOURS., VAPOR DIFFUSION, SITTING DROP,          
REMARK 280  TEMPERATURE 293K                                                    
